					<description><!--[CDATA[<p-->Amir Lerman, M.D., a cardiovascular physician-scientist, mentor, research leader and active Mayo Clinic staff member, passed away Feb. 23 at age 69. During his nearly 40 years at Mayo Clinic, he became one of the world’s foremost authorities on microvascular function and cardiovascular disease. Dr. Lerman earned his doctor of science degree and M.D. in […]<p></p>
